h3. Summary
After upgrading JIRA (e.g. from JIRA 6.3 to 6.4) the *Activity Stream* fails to show Stash's logo. 

h3. Environment
* JIRA 6.3.15
* Stash 3.8.0

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an Application Link between JIRA 6.3.15 and Stash 3.8.0;
# Edit the Project's workflow in JIRA to use a Trigger to transition Open to In Progress (for example) when a commit is created for the issue;
# Commit something on a Stash repository and add a JIRA issue key to the commit comment;
# JIRA will transition the issue to In Progress - Navigate to the Dashboard to see the Activity Stream, which shall be displayed successfully including Stash's logo.
# Stop JIRA and upgrade it to 6.4.1;
# Start JIRA 6.4.1 and navigate to the Dashboard.

h3. Expected Results
JIRA would show the Activity Stream correctly, including Stash's logo.

h3. Actual Results
JIRA shows the Activity Stream, but does not display Stash's logo (returns a 404 error).
The below exception is thrown in the xxxxxxx.log file:
{noformat}
XXXX-XX-XX XX:XX:XX,XXX http-bio-8080-exec-11 INFO xxxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxx XXX.XXX.XXX.XXX,127.0.0.1 /download/resources/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-development-integration-plugin:devstatus-panel-and-dialog-resources/logo_stash96.png [plugin.webresource.servlet.PluginResourceDownload] Could not locate resource: /download/resources/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-development-integration-plugin:devstatus-panel-and-dialog-resources/logo_stash96.png
{noformat}
 
h3. Notes
This appears to happen because in JIRA 6.4.1 JIRA uses a different URL to retrieve the logo:
h5. JIRA 6.3.15:
{noformat:borderStyle=solid| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
http://jira-address/download/resources/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-development-integration-plugin:devstatus-panel-and-dialog-resources/logo_stash96.png?s=48
{noformat}
h5. JIRA 6.4.1:
{noformat:borderStyle=solid| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
http://jira-address/download/resources/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-development-integration-plugin:devstatus-dialog-resources/logo_stash96.png?s=48
{noformat}

h3. Workaround
Keep using JIRA normally as eventually those activities will be replaces by newer ones. New activities will use the correct URLs and consequently display the logo correctly.

